  "description": "A Term is an element of the free algebra T(Σ, X) over a signature Σ and variable set X. It is the canonical syntactic object: built compositionally from variables and operation symbols, characterized by the universal property that any variable assignment into any Σ-algebra extends uniquely to an interpretation of all terms.",
